# World

## Purpose
The ECS backbone. `World` is a singleton that owns the `pg::ecs::Registry` and `pg::ecs::Dispatcher`,
manages all registered systems, and drives the per-frame update cycle. `CheckedRegistryAccessor`
is the only interface through which systems may read or write components; it enforces the
access declarations made in `DeclareAccess()` at runtime.

## Responsibilities
- Owns the single entity/component registry and event dispatcher.
- Accepts system registration via `RegisterSystem`; enforces the one-writer-per-component rule
  at registration time (asserts immediately on violation).
- Derives system execution order from `DeclareAccess` declarations using Kahn's topological sort
  before the first `Update` call.
- Per-frame: flushes the EnTT dispatcher, runs each system in sorted order, destroys all
  event entities (`ClearEvents`), then applies all deferred structural changes
  (`FlushDeferredRequests`).
- Buffers structural changes (add, remove, entity destroy) so they are applied after all systems
  finish iterating — prevents iterator invalidation.

## Key Types

| Type | Role |
|---|---|
| `World` | Singleton; owns registry, dispatcher, system list; drives the frame loop |
| `CheckedRegistryAccessor` | Per-system view of the registry; enforces declared access at runtime |
| `System` | Abstract base; override `Update(Timestep)` and `DeclareAccess()` |
| `SystemAccessDecl` | Declares a system's readSet, writeSet, addSet, inframeAddSet |
| `DeferredRequest` | Internal type-erased buffer entry for deferred structural changes |

## Deferred vs. In-Frame Operations

| Operation | Accessor method | When applied | Visibility |
|---|---|---|---|
| Add component | `EmplaceDeferred` | End of current frame | Next frame |
| Add one-frame component | `EmplaceOneframe` | End of frame; removed end of next frame | One frame |
| Emit event entity | `EmplaceEvent` | End of current frame | Next frame; auto-destroyed |
| Add in-frame component | `EmplaceInframe` | Immediately | Same frame (later systems only) |
| Emit in-frame event | `EmplaceInframeEvent` | Immediately | Same frame; auto-destroyed at frame end |
| Remove component | `RemoveDeferred` | End of current frame | Removed next frame |
| Destroy entity | `DestroyDeferred` | End of current frame (after emplaces) | Destroyed next frame |

## Testing Support
- `UpdateRetainingEvents` (compiled only under `TESTS_ENABLED`): runs one frame exactly like
  `Update` but skips `ClearEvents`, leaving in-frame events in the registry so tests can inspect
  `inframeAddSet` outputs that are otherwise visible only to downstream systems during the frame.

